      "question": "If the $n^{th}$ term of an Arithmetic Progression is given by $a_n = 5 - 3n$, show that the common difference $d$ is $-3$ and find the value of $a_2 - a_1$.",
      "answer": "$d = -3, a_2 - a_1 = -3$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Calculate the first two terms $a_1$ and $a_2$ by substituting $n=1$ and $n=2$ into the expression $a_n = 5 - 3n$.",
          "Calculate the common difference using the definition $d = a_2 - a_1$ and verify that it matches the coefficient of $n$ in the linear expression."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a_n = 5 - 3n \\\\ a_1 = 5 - 3(1) = 2 \\\\ a_2 = 5 - 3(2) = -1 \\\\ d = a_2 - a_1 = -1 - 2 = -3 \\\\ a_2 - a_1 = -3$"
      },
